<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.279991>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9 – 16. Allophrys megafrons sp. nov., Ƥ: 9 — head with antenna, left; 10 — flagellomeres 4 to 6 of antenna, left; 11 — mesosoma, mid and hind legs (tarsi incomplete), and first metasomal segment, left; 12 — apex of metasoma with ovipositor, left. Allophrys noyesi sp. nov., Ƥ: 13 — head with antenna, left. Barycnemis costaricensis sp. nov., Ƥ: 14 — head, mesosoma and first metasomal segment, left; 15 — hind leg (without coxa, tarsus incomplete); 16 — apex of metasoma with ovipositor, left." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/279991/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.279993>
    dc:description "FIGURES 22 – 28. Allophrys bribria sp. nov., Ƥ: 22 — whole insect, left; 23 — head, dorsal. Allophrys compressor sp. nov., Ƥ: 24 — head with antennae, latero-ventro-anterior. Allophrys megafrons sp. nov., Ƥ: 25 — whole insect, left. Allophrys noyesi sp. nov., Ƥ: 26 — whole insect, left; 27 — head, dorsal. Barycnemis costaricensis sp. nov., Ƥ: 28 — whole insect, left." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/279993/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

